The paper deals with the problem of clustering data, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The use of Gaussian mixture models is also a common technique in this field. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves information theory and optimization, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with the behavior of k-means algorithm, which is a popular clustering algorithm, and its analysis, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category.
